<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hey everyone, I am installing arch on a thelio tower by system76 and I am getting errors when trying to connect to wifi</p> <p>What I did:</p> <ul> <li>go to the arch website and pick the latest iso</li> <li>slap it onto a USB</li> <li>boot into the USB</li> <li>connect to wifi using <code>iwctl</code></li> </ul> <p>What happened:</p> <ul> <li>without even running anything I get a ton of issues here they are (<a href="https://imgur.com/a/hON21lB">link</a>)</li> <li>when I run <code>ping</code> <a href="https://google.com"><code>google.com</code></a> <code>-c 3</code> I get two packet losses out of three</li> </ul> <p>It&#39;s important to note that when on the normal system pop-os (the system installed onto the harddrive) I get no errors and 0 packet losses although in that case I am connecting by through the gnome tool</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/spcbfr"> /u/spcbfr </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wg018v/wifi_issues_in_the_live_iso/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wg018v/wifi_issues_in_the_live_iso/">[comments]</a></span>